# Dopamind — Complete Project Context for Cursor

## What Is This App

Dopamind is a gamified ADHD productivity SaaS web app for adults. The core loop is:

- User adds a task
- Picks a focus timer (5/15/25/45/60 min)
- Focuses — a tree grows visually in real time
- Timer completes → tree is saved to their virtual forest
- Abandon the timer → tree dies (dead tree saved)
- Forest grows over days → streak system tracks consistency

Inspired by the Forest app, Habitica, and CBT-based ADHD research. Built for adults with ADHD who struggle with focus, task initiation, and consistency.

**Also referenced in repo:** `CLAUDE.md` (historical ClarifyMind notes); product brand in UI is **Dopamind**.

---

## Stack

| What | Technology |
|------|------------|
| Framework | Next.js 14 App Router |
| Database + Auth | Supabase (PostgreSQL, Frankfurt EU) |
| AI | Groq API — model `llama-3.1-8b-instant` |
| Forest renderer | PixiJS 7.4.2 (WebGL, client-side only) |
| Animation | Framer Motion |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS |
| Language | TypeScript |
| Mobile | Capacitor (wraps Vercel app for Android + iOS) |

**Dev command**

```bash
cd C:\Users\SAHIL\clarifymind\apps\web && npm run dev
```

Local: http://localhost:3000

